<br>
1. Some Monks made an AC check fighting Mobs with different ACvalues. Result was a noticable differenz below 1250 AC and nearly no difference abover 1250 AC.<br>
<br>
That is a tested Part.<br>
<br>
But<br>
<br>
the Problem is that you have to take the AC and the Level and youre Defense in mathematics against the Level of the Mob ant the AtK value of the Mob.<br>
<br>
So each Boss Mob has his own ATK Value and the results are hard hits with 1500 AC or smooth hits with 1500 AC. Most of the Bosses seem to have real high ATK so that the difference between 1500 AC and 1300 AC is not a real thing in preventing from beeing hit hard.<br>
<br>
Other theme is the Exp grinding. There the ATK values of the mobs are way lesser than of the bosses. But with the Softcap at 1250 in the old worlds there is also no real big difference between the Damage taken with 1500 or 1300 AC. There is a bigger difference between 1300 and 1100 AC.<br>
<br>
Until Verant do eliminate the x$%%§$ Softcap on AC there is no real Reason for a Warrior not to hold his AC on some Frontiers ( 1250 AC unbuffed ) up to 1500 AC unbuffed ( when fighing more damaging Mobs ) and take a greater Look at some more HP Parts.<br>
