<br>
SoE prefers to hide the mechanics of the game so that people can &quot;experience&quot; it and feel out the rules for themselves.  Unfortunately, while in real life you can take armour and beat the heck out of it and get some idea as to it's damage protection, in game the effect once you reach a certain AC value dependant upon mob you are up against, or when faced with very high atack mobs regardless of AC is nebulous, and especially coupled with the crappy RNG they use, neigh impossible to parse out with any degree of accuracy.<br>
<br>
If they could get off their high horse and expose the game mechanics that people would reasonably be able to easily evaluate in RL but cannot evaluate in game (similar to the reason they have inspect, to overcome game limitations as to the abililty to observe what people are wearing) then there would be a lot less unrest in the player population, and people would be much less concerned with unintentional or stealth nerfs. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=257207" *****"text-decoration: none">Khuzdul - Cleric</A><br>
